summary:
Here is the summarized content:

The Security Council:
Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, particularly 425 (1978), 426 (1978), 1310 (2000), and 1337 (2001),
 Welcomes the Secretary-General's report on UNIFIL and endorses his observations and recommendations;
 Extends UNIFIL's mandate for 6 months, until 31 January 2002;
 Requests the Secretary-General to implement UNIFIL's reconfiguration and redeployment;
 Reiterates support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty, and political independence;
 Calls on Lebanon to ensure its effective authority in the south, including deployment of Lebanese armed forces;
 Ensures UNIFIL's freedom of movement;
 Encourages a calm environment in the south;
 Reiterates calls on parties to respect the withdrawal line and exercise restraint;
 Condemns violence and urges parties to respect UNIFIL's safety;
 Supports UNIFIL's efforts to maintain the ceasefire;
 Welcomes demining contributions and encourages further assistance;
 Requests the Secretary-General to consult with Lebanon and other parties;
 Looks forward to UNIFIL's early mandate fulfilment;
 Requests a comprehensive report on UNIFIL's activities;
 Stresses the need for a comprehensive, just, and lasting peace in the Middle East.
